race.description: Port Lincoln Cup Carnival 25-27 Feb Maiden Plate
race.comment: HOLDER MAID (9) continued the encouraging form and wasn't far away last time when charging home for third here at the latest. Nice alley and a top chance to break through. RENEGADE CHIEF (6) comes through the same race, beating home HOLDER MAID by half a length after racing much more prominently. Doesn't have to improve much to get the verdict. REIBY PRINCESS (11) has built nicely into this and should be peaking now but is likely to get a long way back from the wide alley. Watch for her charging late. NOUVEAU MARCHE (5) resumes and looks to be in good order after placing in a trial. Can make his presence felt fresh. MACSPARK (4) has mixed his form in three runs back but there are glimpses. Keeping safe.
